				You guys missed the point.<BR>
<BR>
The problem is simple and Absor explained it quite well, but the solution they are taking is a lazy one and only shows who their interest goes to. I will explain this later on.<BR>
<BR>
1) The more time goes, the more clerics are levelling and are elligible to make their FA quest.<BR>
<BR>
2) The FA quests were designed to make ppl loot stuffs on particular mobs that were TOUGH to kill at that time (nearly one year ago), only the very best had enough ressources to do it, therefore, a very few attempted to complete the quest, kill the right mobs and so. There were maybe less than 5 clerics by servers elligible (read : leveled enough and in ubber guild) to complete their FA.<BR>
<BR>
3) Now, every good guild, not just the ubbers, can kill those mobs. From the 5 clerics of the start, you now have more than a hundred, wanting to kill the same mobs (with sometimes a weekly spawn rate). It's simply not feasible anymore, because the competition is too hard, unless you are the luckyiest man on earth.<BR>
<BR>
4) This game can't adapt itself with his player base and Verant's staff can't make quick changes to make the game matches its public demand. Plus, they are just trying to keep their ubbers-hardcore gamers in the game, because each one of them have 3 or 4 accounts and are generating much publicity with their website and general fame. And ubbers already have their FA, they don't need nor want more and have already moved on other ubber stuffs.<BR>
<BR>
5) They don't want that every single guy in the game possesses its FA weapon once he reaches the appropriate level because they should be artifact.<BR>
Thus, only the ubbers (read : The top 3 or so guilds on each server) are privileged with the best equipment and this matter of fact is agravated as time goes on.<BR>
<BR>
6) The game is broken and only the ubbers are playing it in &quot;Verant's vision&quot;, that is : To be completly time-dedicated to EQ.<BR>
Some of them are/were earning enough bucks to live from it just by selling PLed chars on eBay.<BR>
<BR>
'kay enough for now. No rants intended. Just plain facts.
