				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Stuck with this game??!?!?<BR>
I'm sorry.  I will untie you from your chair so you can stop playing.<BR>
You are playing 'cause you want to play.<BR>
If you did not enjoy it, you wouldn't play.<BR>
<BR>
And as for increasing the supply to meet the demand?  Sorry, that logic doesn't work.  The problem is that everyone wants the best.  If everyone has the best, then everyone will want something better or Verant will have to make the game harder.<BR>
Think of it like this.  You want to be paid more for your job.  Should your employer pay you more just because you want more?  No.  Only the people who are willing to work harder will get paid more.  But lets just say he does.  Then everyone wants more.  Then everyone gets paid more.  Then prices go up and you are right back where you started.<BR>
The long and short of it is:<BR>
If you don't like the game, don't play.<BR>
If you want something tough to get, then expect it to be tough to get, don't demand that it be made easier to get.<BR>
